<br>
Course others say 3 days +/- 12 hrs..... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=malakriss>Malakriss</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 308<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 8:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BG Spawn Question</span><hr size=1> I believe it is 36 hours +/- 12 hours after a patch, then 72 hours +/- 12 hours on respawn.  *However* there is a script to reset Plane of Fear that is rarely known and hardly ever used.  Mainly because the people that do know don't want to spend 1-2 hours every day clearing green trash mobs with minibosses that DT just for Cazic loot, but they certainly don't want to have people repopping it or griefing others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balicosdalinar>Balicos Dalinar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 9:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BG Spawn Question</span><hr size=1> My guild doesnt do Fear anymore, Emp and VT keys are our focus atm. Its very hard to get a tracker into Fear to see if BG is up, I know if he was up Id have a better chance of getting some forces to head there for the kill. With that said, would a 59 wizard have much of a chance of sucesfully getting in and to the BG spawn to check if hes up? I also have  a 47 SK but I would think that he would get a heck of alot low level aggro. Any suggestions? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/napalm2/gumbum/balicos.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr>